<LegalPageLayout
	title="Privacy Policy — Simbi: Bedtime Stories"
	heading="Privacy Policy"
	subtitle="How we collect, use, and protect your information."
	description="Privacy Policy for Simbi: Bedtime Stories. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your information."
	lastUpdated="28 March 2026"
>

<p>Simbi: Bedtime Stories ("Simbi", "we", "us", or "our") respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, and share information when you use our mobile application, website, and related services (together, the "Services").</p>

<p>If you do not agree with this Privacy Policy, please do not use the Services.</p>

<h2>1. Who we are</h2>
<div class="contact-block">
	<span class="contact-name">Matthew Smart</span>
	<span>Email: <a href="mailto:support@getsimbi.com">support@getsimbi.com</a></span>
	<span>Website: <a href="https://getsimbi.com">getsimbi.com</a></span>
</div>

<h2>2. Who this policy applies to</h2>
<p>Simbi is designed for families and may be used by parents, guardians, and children under adult supervision. We aim to collect only the information reasonably necessary to provide the service.</p>

<h2>3. Information we collect</h2>
<p>We may collect the following categories of information:</p>

<h3>A. Account information</h3>
<ul>
	<li>Name</li>
	<li>Email address</li>
	<li>Login credentials or authentication identifiers</li>
	<li>Subscription status</li>
</ul>

<h3>B. Child profile information</h3>
<p>If you create a child profile in the app, we may collect information you choose to provide, such as:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Child nickname or first name</li>
	<li>Age or age range</li>
	<li>Avatar selections</li>
	<li>Story preferences, themes, helpers, or favorites</li>
</ul>
<p>We ask that you do not provide sensitive personal information about a child.</p>

<h3>C. Story generation information</h3>
<p>To generate personalized bedtime stories, we may process:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Prompts you submit</li>
	<li>Character details you enter</li>
	<li>Story settings and preferences</li>
	<li>Saved stories, audio preferences, and playback activity</li>
</ul>

<h3>D. Purchase and subscription information</h3>
<p>If you subscribe or make purchases, payment processing is handled by Apple. We do not receive your full payment card details. We may receive information such as:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Subscription tier</li>
	<li>Product purchased</li>
	<li>Renewal or cancellation status</li>
	<li>Transaction identifiers or entitlement status</li>
</ul>

<h3>E. Device and usage information</h3>
<p>We may automatically collect limited technical information such as:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Device type</li>
	<li>App version</li>
	<li>Operating system</li>
	<li>Crash diagnostics</li>
	<li>Basic usage events</li>
</ul>

<h3>F. Support communications</h3>
<p>If you contact us, we may collect:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Your name</li>
	<li>Email address</li>
	<li>The contents of your message</li>
	<li>Any attachments or screenshots you send</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. How we use information</h2>
<p>We use information to:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Provide and operate Simbi</li>
	<li>Create and deliver personalized bedtime stories and audio</li>
	<li>Maintain accounts and subscriptions</li>
	<li>Save story history and preferences</li>
	<li>Improve app performance, reliability, and safety</li>
	<li>Respond to support requests</li>
	<li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
	<li>Prevent fraud, abuse, or misuse of the Services</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Legal bases for processing</h2>
<p>Where applicable under UK GDPR or similar laws, we process personal data on one or more of the following bases:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Performance of a contract</li>
	<li>Legitimate interests</li>
	<li>Consent</li>
	<li>Compliance with legal obligations</li>
</ul>

<h2>6. How we share information</h2>
<p>We do not sell personal information.</p>
<p>We may share information with trusted service providers only as necessary to operate the Services, such as:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Cloud hosting and database providers</li>
	<li>Authentication providers</li>
	<li>Analytics and crash reporting providers</li>
	<li>Subscription and purchase infrastructure providers</li>
	<li>AI or voice generation providers used to create story or audio content</li>
	<li>Customer support tools</li>
</ul>
<p>These providers are only permitted to use information on our behalf and as needed to provide their services to us.</p>

<h2>7. AI-generated content</h2>
<p>Simbi may use third-party AI or voice technology to generate story text, narration, or related features. Information you submit for story creation may be processed by those providers solely to generate and return the requested content and to improve service reliability, subject to their applicable terms and privacy practices.</p>

<h2>8. Children's privacy</h2>
<p>We take children's privacy seriously.</p>
<p>Simbi is intended to be used by a parent or guardian, or with appropriate parental involvement. We do not knowingly collect more personal information from children than is reasonably necessary for the app's functionality.</p>
<p>Parents or guardians may contact us to:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Request access to personal data associated with their account</li>
	<li>Request correction of inaccurate information</li>
	<li>Request deletion of account or child profile data</li>
</ul>
<p>If you believe a child has provided personal information inappropriately, contact us at <a href="mailto:support@getsimbi.com">support@getsimbi.com</a>.</p>

<h2>9. Data retention</h2>
<p>We keep information only for as long as needed to:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Provide the Services</li>
	<li>Maintain your account</li>
	<li>Comply with legal, tax, or regulatory obligations</li>
	<li>Resolve disputes and enforce our agreements</li>
</ul>
<p>If you request deletion, we will delete or anonymize your information unless we are legally required to retain certain records.</p>

<h2>10. Your rights</h2>
<p>Depending on your location, you may have rights to:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Access your personal data</li>
	<li>Correct inaccurate data</li>
	<li>Delete your data</li>
	<li>Object to certain processing</li>
	<li>Restrict certain processing</li>
	<li>Request portability of your data</li>
	<li>Withdraw consent where processing is based on consent</li>
</ul>
<p>To exercise these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:support@getsimbi.com">support@getsimbi.com</a>.</p>

<h2>11. Data deletion and privacy choices</h2>
<p>You can request account deletion or make privacy-related requests by:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Using the deletion feature inside the app, where available</li>
	<li>Visiting our <a href="/privacy-choices">Privacy Choices</a> page</li>
	<li>Contacting us at <a href="mailto:support@getsimbi.com">support@getsimbi.com</a></li>
</ul>

<h2>12. International data transfers</h2>
<p>Your information may be processed in countries outside your country of residence. Where required, we take reasonable steps to ensure appropriate safeguards are in place.</p>

<h2>13. Security</h2>
<p>We use reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect information. However, no system is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

<h2>14. Third-party services and links</h2>
<p>Our Services may rely on or link to third-party services. Their privacy practices are governed by their own policies, not ours.</p>

<h2>15. Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>
<p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make material changes, we will update the "Last updated" date and may provide additional notice where appropriate.</p>

<h2>16. Contact us</h2>
<p>If you have questions or privacy requests, contact:</p>
<div class="contact-block">
	<span class="contact-name">Matthew Smart</span>
	<span><a href="mailto:support@getsimbi.com">support@getsimbi.com</a></span>
</div>

</LegalPageLayout>
